-- Kouvelis Says Government’s Task to Hold Greek Elections June 17
-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 2012-05-16T11:35:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/kouvelis-says-government-s-task-to-hold-greek-elections-june-17.html
Greece ’s Democratic Left leader Fotis Kouvelis said the new caretaker government decided by party
leaders today would have one task, that of holding elections. He
said elections would most likely be held on June 17.  He spoke to reporters in Athens in comments carried live on
state-run NET TV.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  